commit.message:
Reimplement the divmod() C integer optimisation using dynamic code generation.

See https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6717
Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6786
Do not doubly report errors due to fused types.
Add divmod() support for C floating point. The calculation is always in double, as Python divmod().
Allow calling divmod() on C number types without GIL.
Allow the first operant to implement its own "__divmod__" even if the second operand is a float. Only optimise safe cases.
Avoid unnecessary checks in normal (1-level typedef) cases.
